In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Core, deseed, and dice @Green Bell Pepper{1} into 1/2-inch pieces. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary; cut crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1}. Peel and grate or mince @Ginger{1%thumb}. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{4%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #large pan{} for 4 servings). Add bell pepper, green beans, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are slightly softened and lightly charred, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add another large drizzle of oil to pan with veggies; stir in shallot, ginger, and half the @Curry Powder{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings). Cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add @Coconut Milk{1}. (TIP: Thoroughly shake coconut milk in container before opening.) Stir in @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1}, juice from half the lime, and @Sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4). Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium low.

Simmer curry until sauce has thickened and veggies are tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in half the cilantro. Taste and season with @salt{} and more lime juice if desired. Turn off heat.

Roughly chop @Peanuts{1/2%ounce}. Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} or #plates{} and top with curry. Garnish with peanuts and remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.